# URLs the link checker must skip. Each entry is a regex, and each needs a reason —
# an unexplained entry here is indistinguishable from hiding a genuinely broken link.

# GitHub's user-attachments assets (the README's hero image) 302-redirect to a signed
# S3 URL, and lychee fails on it with "HTTP/2 protocol error. Server may not support
# HTTP/2 properly". The asset is not broken — verified directly:
#
#   curl --http1.1 -L …/assets/c637c97e-… -> 200, image/png, 1431187 bytes
#   curl --http2   -L …/assets/c637c97e-… -> 200
#
# The redirect target also carries a five-minute expiring signature, so these URLs can
# never be checked reliably no matter how the protocol behaves.
https://github\.com/user-attachments/
